<task id="041" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build GetStartedCardsWidget — 7-card 2-col grid (FR-18)</title>
    <phase>Phase D — Context pane</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>012</dependencies>
    <blocks>042</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, fluent-ui, ai</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Net-new context widget that becomes the welcome-state landing in the Context pane. Consumes the ActionCard primitive (potentially lifted to @spaarke/ui-components in task 012) — ADR-012 (load-bearing) compliance is in scope. Touches the PaneEventBus dispatch path (wiring detail completed in task 042). Multi-FR composite (FR-18) with accessibility + dark-mode bars.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>D</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build the new `GetStartedCardsWidget` per FR-18: a 7-card, 2-column scrollable grid
    rendered on the Context pane's welcome stage. Each card reuses the LegalWorkspace
    `ActionCard` primitive (import path determined by task 012 outcome — either lifted to
    `@spaarke/ui-components` or still in LegalWorkspace). Cards: Create Matter, Create
    Project, Assign Work, Summarize Files, Find Similar, Send Email, Schedule Meeting.
    Each card onClick will eventually dispatch a `widget_load` event on the `workspace`
    PaneEventBus channel — wire onClick callbacks now, but the actual dispatch wiring is
    completed in task 042. Keyboard navigation (arrow keys + Enter), Fluent v9 tokens
    only, dark-mode safe.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React 19 + Fluent v9 frontend developer experienced with `makeStyles` + Fluent design
    tokens, CSS grid layouts, accessible keyboard navigation, and composable widget
    primitives. Familiar with the @spaarke/ui-components consumption pattern and ADR-012
    "shared components live in the shared lib" rule.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new file `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/context/GetStartedCardsWidget.tsx`
    exists and exports `GetStartedCardsWidget` (a React component). It renders 7 ActionCard
    instances in a CSS grid with `gridTemplateColumns: '1fr 1fr'` and `gap: tokens.spacingHorizontalS`,
    vertically scrollable on overflow. Each card has a Fluent v9 icon + label per the FR-19
    mapping. Each card accepts an optional `onCardClick(widgetType: string)` callback (wired in
    task 042). Cards are keyboard-navigable (arrow keys + Enter to activate). The widget
    matches LegalWorkspace ActionCard styling exactly. Works in both light and dark modes
    via Fluent v9 tokens.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-18 introduces the GetStartedCardsWidget that replaces PlaybookGalleryWidget on the
      welcome stage of the Context pane. Per OC-04 + ADR-012, the ActionCard primitive is
      reused (lifted to @spaarke/ui-components in task 012 if needed; otherwise imported
      from LegalWorkspace). The 7 cards each trigger a different wizard widget in the
      Workspace pane via PaneEventBus `widget_load` events on the `workspace` channel — the
      wiring is finalized in task 042 (which also registers this widget in
      ContextWidgetRegistry). This task focuses on the widget component itself (markup,
      styling, accessibility) — the event-dispatch wiring is a thin callback that task 042
      plugs in.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/context/GetStartedCardsWidget.tsx</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">ActionCard primitive is consumed from `@spaarke/ui-components` if task 012 lifted it there, OR from the LegalWorkspace path if task 012 verified it as context-agnostic without lifting. Do NOT copy-paste ActionCard logic. Read task 012 completion notes / `current-task.md` to determine the correct import path.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 tokens only. Grid spacing uses `tokens.spacingHorizontalS`. No hex literals, no `rgba(...)` literals, no Fluent v8. Card icon colors use semantic Fluent tokens (typically `colorBrandForeground1`).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 only. Use `makeStyles` from `@fluentui/react-components` for styling. No CSS-in-JS libraries outside Fluent.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-025">All card icons come from `@fluentui/react-icons` (Fluent v9). Suggested icons: `DocumentAddRegular` (Create Matter), `FolderAddRegular` (Create Project), `TaskListSquareLtrRegular` or `PeopleAddRegular` (Assign Work), `DocumentMultipleRegular` (Summarize Files), `SearchRegular` (Find Similar), `MailRegular` (Send Email), `CalendarLtrRegular` (Schedule Meeting). No new SVG web resources.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No `accessToken` props or state. This widget does NOT make BFF calls directly — it only dispatches PaneEventBus events. Any future BFF interaction MUST go through `authenticatedFetch`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">2-column CSS grid layout (`gridTemplateColumns: '1fr 1fr'`); `gap: spacingHorizontalS`; vertical scroll on overflow; keyboard-navigable; matches LegalWorkspace card styling exactly.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">This task creates the widget COMPONENT only. Registration in `ContextWidgetRegistry` and the welcome-stage swap are in task 042. Wire `onCardClick` as a callback prop now; task 042 plugs in the PaneEventBus dispatcher.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/plan.md</file>
